            "answer_text": "Singles: one released song. Usually a title track in the album, if it released into an album, though. It\u2019s used as their main track promotion. Mini albums: it\u2019s actually the same as usual album. But only have like 5\u20136 songs in it. That\u2019s why it\u2019s called mini. Albums: I am thinking you\u2019re saying it as a full studio album. A full studio album is an album where the track inside has around 10 or more songs. Repackaged album: a slightly different version of the original album. It\u2019s usually has same tracks inside the CD, with some adding few more songs and have a different title track to promote. ",
